1664
02:07:20,940 --> 02:07:24,940
but maybe 61 years of, maybe, 61.

1665
02:07:24,940 --> 02:07:31,940
Yeah, it'll be 60. This is, it'll be 61, right?

1666
02:07:31,940 --> 02:07:35,940
Yeah. No. It'll be this 60 second anniversary.

1667
02:07:35,940 --> 02:07:42,940
And you're as big to that's 50 years to 2010. So it's 62 this fall.

1668
02:07:42,940 --> 02:07:44,940
Yeah. Yeah.

1669
02:07:44,940 --> 02:07:47,940
It's just remarkable.

1670
02:07:47,940 --> 02:07:55,940
You have forged this partnership as a, as a, as a, quote, interracial couple since we have this concept of race that has defined.

1671
02:07:55,940 --> 02:07:58,940
Yeah. Right.

1672
02:07:58,940 --> 02:08:03,940
And I would invite your reflections on that experience too.

1673
02:08:03,940 --> 02:08:08,940
I know, Priscilla, you had mentioned in the break, but that was something that you wanted to touch on.

1674
02:08:08,940 --> 02:08:16,940
Well, I did. I do remember what Dr. Dubois said.

1675
02:08:16,940 --> 02:08:23,940
And it probably was after the loving, loving decision, Loving v. Virginia,

1676
02:08:23,940 --> 02:08:29,940
that overturned all the miscegenation laws in the country.

1677
02:08:29,940 --> 02:08:36,940
I think there were 17 states that still had miscegenation laws.

1678
02:08:36,940 --> 02:08:50,940
And he was a leader in the NAACP and he, he made the statement that the NAACP did not support,

1679
02:08:50,940 --> 02:08:57,940
it did not oppose interracial marriage and it did not support interracial marriage.

1680
02:08:57,940 --> 02:09:06,940
It believed that individuals who fall in love should have the right to pursue their relationships.

1681
02:09:06,940 --> 02:09:19,940
And that's the way I felt about it. I mean, we didn't fall in love and get married and have three children in order to create some new racial groupings.

1682
02:09:19,940 --> 02:09:32,940
So, grouping in this country, some people talk about the elimination of race by consolidation or, you know, come on.

1683
02:09:32,940 --> 02:09:37,940
We have to respect cultural differences and so on.

1684
02:09:37,940 --> 02:09:48,940
Our older daughter once told us that she thought the reason that we had such a long marriage was because of our moral compass.

1685
02:09:48,940 --> 02:09:58,940
And that it, we came from very different backgrounds and so on, but somehow or rather we had the same goals.

1686
02:09:58,940 --> 02:10:03,940
So there you go. How about that?

1687
02:10:03,940 --> 02:10:06,940
That sounds very reasonable.

1688
02:10:06,940 --> 02:10:12,940
Well, you might have come in for a little criticism of how to fight out.

1689
02:10:12,940 --> 02:10:17,940
But of course, you're family as we have studied more about his family.

1690
02:10:17,940 --> 02:10:25,940
There has been quite a lot of interracial relationship.

1691
02:10:25,940 --> 02:10:33,940
Including the Alamo. I don't know quite figure that one out, but.

1692
02:10:34,940 --> 02:10:42,940
Well, he has listed as one of, well, Paul and that is true.

1693
02:10:42,940 --> 02:10:45,940
Yeah.

1694
02:10:45,940 --> 02:10:55,940
Paul and Paul and that is son, but I don't know much about Paul and that, who was my great-great-grandmother.

1695
02:10:55,940 --> 02:11:05,940
I don't know where she came from, but I was told that she came from a very wealthy family of the travestists around Richmond.

1696
02:11:05,940 --> 02:11:10,940
So I hate to put her into the Richmond mat.

1697
02:11:10,940 --> 02:11:13,940
Dr. Bass, I want to ask a final question of you.

1698
02:11:13,940 --> 02:11:22,940
I'd be interested to hear about your service on the Human Rights Commission in New York City.

1699
02:11:22,940 --> 02:11:29,940
Well, I mean, we met about every month. I think it was every month.

1700
02:11:29,940 --> 02:11:32,940
We're not too often.

1701
02:11:32,940 --> 02:11:37,940
And what I would do is to check up and see.

1702
02:11:37,940 --> 02:11:43,940
See, we had several neighborhood groups in our community.

1703
02:11:43,940 --> 02:11:47,940
Which were well organized, like Reena.

1704
02:11:47,940 --> 02:11:58,940
They had group, housing group, and that was the group down in the in-house going east.

1705
02:11:58,940 --> 02:12:02,940
421, was that right? 421?

1706
02:12:02,940 --> 02:12:12,940
Yeah, they had gotten some, in which some group, I don't remember the name, they were trying to get something done about housing in the neighborhood.

1707
02:12:12,940 --> 02:12:17,940
So I used to look at, see how those cases were proceeding.

1708
02:12:17,940 --> 02:12:21,940
That was my main interest in going to these meetings.

1709
02:12:21,940 --> 02:12:28,940
Because we always had big dinners. I have cards where we used to meet at what's the big house?

1710
02:12:28,940 --> 02:12:29,940
Plaza.

1711
02:12:29,940 --> 02:12:30,940
That's the big house.

1712
02:12:30,940 --> 02:12:31,940
You know.

1713
02:12:31,940 --> 02:12:33,940
It used to meet there.

1714
02:12:33,940 --> 02:12:38,940
So I think the governor gave us a lot of money to run that old.

1715
02:12:38,940 --> 02:12:41,940
Because I never paid for it.

1716
02:12:41,940 --> 02:12:48,940
But I mean, I think this vagueness is an indication of the effectiveness.

1717
02:12:48,940 --> 02:12:49,940
Let's pause.

1718
02:12:49,940 --> 02:12:50,940
Just a second.

1719
02:12:50,940 --> 02:12:51,940
Yeah, put up.

1720
02:12:51,940 --> 02:12:52,940
We were married.

1721
02:12:52,940 --> 02:13:08,940
Back, Basit, I think you wanted to kind of sum up your perspective on the merits or impacts or lack thereof of the Human Rights Commission.

1722
02:13:08,940 --> 02:13:23,940
I'm trying to wonder, I'm thinking about where should I start?

1723
02:13:23,940 --> 02:13:25,940
The Human Rights Commission.

1724
02:13:25,940 --> 02:13:31,940
Well, I mean, the one I'm working with now, you know, the county's broke.

1725
02:13:31,940 --> 02:13:32,940
Jobs.

1726
02:13:32,940 --> 02:13:47,940
They go to the people who have the inside information and you're somebody to refer them to the proper, to the job.

1727
02:13:47,940 --> 02:13:55,940
Now, in New York City, I guess it's the political club that will get you a job.

1728
02:13:55,940 --> 02:13:58,940
Sometimes, not always, but sometimes.

1729
02:13:58,940 --> 02:14:09,940
So those are the things that I see and that can be very difficult to get ahead there.

1730
02:14:09,940 --> 02:14:14,940
Now, I never had those problems because I was never looking for a city job.

1731
02:14:14,940 --> 02:14:22,940
And I was always able to get a job if I wanted a job.

1732
02:14:22,940 --> 02:14:32,940
But I did go to these Dairy Technology big places.

1733
02:14:32,940 --> 02:14:38,940
And there, they were not willing to give you a job.

1734
02:14:38,940 --> 02:14:50,940
Although their plants were right in the middle of the black community and not even a porter or a sweeper or anybody.

1735
02:14:50,940 --> 02:14:51,940
They were black.

1736
02:14:51,940 --> 02:14:54,940
That was Beatrice Foods.

1737
02:14:54,940 --> 02:14:56,940
1950.

1738
02:14:56,940 --> 02:14:57,940
No.

1739
02:14:57,940 --> 02:14:58,940
No.

1740
02:14:58,940 --> 02:14:59,940
55.

1741
02:14:59,940 --> 02:15:10,940
And also, one of my professors had a brother that worked there.

1742
02:15:10,940 --> 02:15:14,940
He thought I should have told him what color I was before I came.

1743
02:15:14,940 --> 02:15:16,940
I said, well, they didn't ask.

1744
02:15:16,940 --> 02:15:18,940
So why should I volunteer?

1745
02:15:18,940 --> 02:15:23,940
They would see me when I came.

1746
02:15:23,940 --> 02:15:25,940
That's what I got.

1747
02:15:25,940 --> 02:15:29,940
You know, he talked as if he could soften the way for you.

1748
02:15:29,940 --> 02:15:32,940
His brother, since he had a brother, had a job.

1749
02:15:32,940 --> 02:15:35,940
And they both had gone to Purdue.

1750
02:15:35,940 --> 02:15:45,940
And his father was head of the Dairy Technology Department at Purdue College of Agriculture.

1751
02:15:45,940 --> 02:15:54,940
So I don't know whether Jim, but when I left Ohio State University, they got rid of their technology.

1752
02:15:54,940 --> 02:16:00,940
They got rid of food technology and made it into some...

1753
02:16:00,940 --> 02:16:02,940
What do they call it now?

1754
02:16:02,940 --> 02:16:04,940
Food technology.

1755
02:16:04,940 --> 02:16:07,940
No, the science is food science.

1756
02:16:07,940 --> 02:16:08,940
Food science.

1757
02:16:08,940 --> 02:16:11,940
They all were put into food sciences.

1758
02:16:11,940 --> 02:16:16,940
So they got rid of Dr. Gould who was head of Dairy Technology.

1759
02:16:16,940 --> 02:16:20,940
And death rich, that was biochemistry.

1760
02:16:20,940 --> 02:16:24,940
It was also combined with health science.

1761
02:16:24,940 --> 02:16:25,940
Yeah.

1762
02:16:25,940 --> 02:16:26,940
Yeah.

1763
02:16:26,940 --> 02:16:29,940
The three things were combined.

1764
02:16:29,940 --> 02:16:40,940
I know you've written elsewhere noted that you were much motivated by Frederick Douglass' observation

1765
02:16:40,940 --> 02:16:43,940
that without struggle, there is no progress.

1766
02:16:43,940 --> 02:16:51,940
You have paid long pads of a great deal of social justice struggle on many fronts.

1767
02:16:51,940 --> 02:16:57,940
So I'm glad we've had this occasion to visit and document at least a little bit of that work

1768
02:16:57,940 --> 02:17:01,940
and in a little bit of time we could be together because there's such a long record of service.

1769
02:17:01,940 --> 02:17:05,940
So it's a real honor and a privilege to be with you both.

1770
02:17:05,940 --> 02:17:06,940
Thank you.

1771
02:17:06,940 --> 02:17:10,940
You're honored to have participated in this discussion.

1772
02:17:10,940 --> 02:17:18,940
It makes me a little introspective after we look back and see where I didn't do what I should have done.

1773
02:17:18,940 --> 02:17:21,940
I don't know if it's bad or I'm not sure if it's the best.

1774
02:17:21,940 --> 02:17:23,940
Any final thoughts?

1775
02:17:23,940 --> 02:17:27,940
I remember when I first went to register the vote.

1776
02:17:27,940 --> 02:17:32,940
That was just before I went into the Army.

1777
02:17:32,940 --> 02:17:37,940
I went to a little field in the station about two miles from home.

1778
02:17:37,940 --> 02:17:40,940
That's where they registered voters.

1779
02:17:40,940 --> 02:17:43,940
So I told him who I was.

1780
02:17:43,940 --> 02:17:49,940
And he went, I thought he was going to give me an application to fill out.

1781
02:17:49,940 --> 02:17:51,940
That was my assumption.

1782
02:17:51,940 --> 02:17:55,940
But he just gave me an empty sheet of paper.

1783
02:17:55,940 --> 02:17:58,940
He said, go ahead and register yourself there.

1784
02:17:58,940 --> 02:18:03,940
So my father was dead by then because he always voted.

1785
02:18:03,940 --> 02:18:06,940
He probably would have told me what to do.

1786
02:18:06,940 --> 02:18:12,940
But I talked with another man a week or so before I went up there.

1787
02:18:12,940 --> 02:18:16,940
And he had told me his name was Jim Mullins.

1788
02:18:16,940 --> 02:18:20,940
He was a pretty well off black band in the community.

1789
02:18:20,940 --> 02:18:22,940
And I'd run into a lot of problems.

1790
02:18:22,940 --> 02:18:25,940
He ran the corn meal.

1791
02:18:25,940 --> 02:18:30,940
And everybody went to that black white or everybody went to that.

1792
02:18:30,940 --> 02:18:33,940
And they were corned and they corned me up.

1793
02:18:33,940 --> 02:18:40,940
And he told me, he said, just think about an application that you were feeling.

1794
02:18:40,940 --> 02:18:44,940
That you want to identify yourself to somebody.

1795
02:18:44,940 --> 02:18:48,940
And put on there when you were born.

1796
02:18:48,940 --> 02:18:53,940
And I think he might have told me to put on there my race.

1797
02:18:53,940 --> 02:18:57,940
But somehow, that's one thing I left all, I don't know,

1798
02:18:57,940 --> 02:19:00,940
whether that just never came to me.

1799
02:19:00,940 --> 02:19:05,940
I told him when I was born, who my mother was, who my father was,

1800
02:19:05,940 --> 02:19:09,940
where they lived, where they were born.

1801
02:19:09,940 --> 02:19:12,940
I told him all of those things.

1802
02:19:12,940 --> 02:19:15,940
So he called me back, but he says, you never put on there.

1803
02:19:15,940 --> 02:19:17,940
You were black.

1804
02:19:17,940 --> 02:19:19,940
I said, do I need to put that there?

1805
02:19:19,940 --> 02:19:21,940
You can see I am.

1806
02:19:21,940 --> 02:19:24,940
And he says, just sign it there.

1807
02:19:24,940 --> 02:19:27,940
You belong.

1808
02:19:27,940 --> 02:19:30,940
I guess at that time they put Negro.

1809
02:19:30,940 --> 02:19:33,940
I think so.

1810
02:19:33,940 --> 02:19:35,940
That was 40.

1811
02:19:35,940 --> 02:19:38,940
I guess that must have been about 42 or 3.

1812
02:19:38,940 --> 02:19:41,940
So I did put Negro.

1813
02:19:41,940 --> 02:19:43,940
And they registered you?

1814
02:19:43,940 --> 02:19:44,940
Yeah, registered.

1815
02:19:44,940 --> 02:19:47,940
No problem.

1816
02:19:47,940 --> 02:19:53,940
And that's, I guess, a lot of people can hardly feel I was an application.

1817
02:19:53,940 --> 02:19:58,940
A lot of people who haven't been to college or finished high school,

1818
02:19:58,940 --> 02:20:01,940
at least, wouldn't know how to do that.

1819
02:20:01,940 --> 02:20:04,940
But I did all of that.

1820
02:20:04,940 --> 02:20:10,940
And where I went to school, all of that.

1821
02:20:10,940 --> 02:20:13,940
He just looked at him and said, this is fine,

1822
02:20:13,940 --> 02:20:17,940
except you didn't put your race.

1823
02:20:17,940 --> 02:20:19,940
Thank you both so very much.

1824
02:20:19,940 --> 02:20:20,940
It's been a real privilege.

1825
02:20:20,940 --> 02:20:21,940
Thank you.

1826
02:20:21,940 --> 02:20:24,940
Thank you very much.

1827
02:20:24,940 --> 02:20:28,940
This has been a presentation of the Library of Congress

1828
02:20:28,940 --> 02:20:33,940
and the Smithsonian National Museum of African American History and Culture.

